content: On September 18, 1993, the Atlanta Braves celebrated a significant milestone as they clinched the National League West title with a 5-2 victory over the San Francisco Giants at Turner Field. This victory marked the Braves' second consecutive division title and was pivotal in their run that would lead to an impressive stretch of 14 consecutive division championships. Tom Glavine, who pitched a complete game, was instrumental in securing the win, showcasing the team's dominant pitching staff during the early '90s.
